LIMITED RESEARCH PERMISSION

Permission is granted to access and examine publicly released VGUFT materials
for personal study, academic evaluation, criticism, commentary, and
noncommercial research.

Users may:

1. Read and download publicly released materials for personal or internal research.
2. Cite VGUFT publications using accurate authorship, title, version, and source information.
3. Quote limited portions where permitted by applicable law.
4. Conduct private, noncommercial calculations, tests, replications, and evaluations.
5. Submit proposed corrections, extensions, experiments, code, or documentation through official VGUFT contribution channels.


RIGHTS NOT GRANTED

Except where required by applicable law, no permission is granted to:

1. Sell, license, monetize, sublicense, or commercially exploit VGUFT materials.
2. Republish, mirror, or redistribute complete VGUFT works or substantial portions of them, except as inherent to the hosting platform's own access and fork functionality.
3. Distribute modified, translated, adapted, or derivative versions of protected VGUFT materials.
4. Incorporate VGUFT source code, documentation, figures, datasets, or protected expression into another product, service, publication, model, or commercial research program.
5. Use VGUFT materials for paid products, consulting, commercial training, proprietary software, or revenue-generating services.
6. Use VGUFT materials as training data, fine-tuning data, retrieval data, or evaluation data for a commercial artificial-intelligence system without written permission.
7. Remove or alter copyright, attribution, version, provenance, or rights notices.
8. Use the names "VGUFT," "Vacuum Grand Unified Fluid Theory," associated logos, seals, or project branding in a manner that suggests sponsorship, authorization, affiliation, or official status.
9. Represent any modification, fork, extension, or interpretation as an official VGUFT publication or approved component.
10. Grant any third party rights in VGUFT materials.


CONTRIBUTIONS

Submission of material does not guarantee acceptance, authorship credit,
project membership, ownership, or inclusion in an official release.

No contribution will be incorporated into the official VGUFT project until the
contributor has accepted the applicable Contributor Agreement and the
