Permission requests must identify:

- The requesting person or organization.
- The materials requested.
- The proposed use.
- Whether the use is commercial, institutional, governmental, or nonprofit.
- The intended audience and distribution method.
- Any expected revenue, funding, compensation, or commercial benefit.

No permission is valid unless granted in a signed written agreement by an
authorized VGUFT representative.


